Har linked list question ka base ye hai:

Node* temp = head;

while(temp != NULL) {
    // kaam yaha karo
    temp = temp->next;
}


âš ï¸ temp = temp->next; kabhi mat bhoolna.

ðŸ§  2ï¸âƒ£ Insert Template (1-based position)
Node* insert(Node* head, int pos, int val) {

    Node* newNode = new Node(val);

    if(pos == 1) {
        newNode->next = head;
        return newNode;
    }

    Node* temp = head;

    for(int i = 1; i < pos - 1; i++)
        temp = temp->next;

    newNode->next = temp->next;
    temp->next = newNode;

    return head;
}


ðŸ‘‰ Pattern yaad rakho:

newNode->next = temp->next;
temp->next = newNode;

ðŸ§  3ï¸âƒ£ Delete Template (1-based position)
Node* deleteNode(Node* head, int pos) {

    if(pos == 1)
        return head->next;

    Node* temp = head;

    for(int i = 1; i < pos - 1; i++)
        temp = temp->next;

    temp->next = temp->next->next;

    return head;
}


ðŸ‘‰ Pattern yaad rakho:

temp->next = temp->next->next;

ðŸ§  4ï¸âƒ£ Count / Search Template
int count(Node* head, int key) {

    int cnt = 0;
    Node* temp = head;

    while(temp != NULL) {
        if(temp->data == key)
            cnt++;

        temp = temp->next;
    }

    return cnt;
}

ðŸ”¥ Golden Rules (Exam/Interview Hack)

Head change ho sakta hai â†’ return head.

Position 1-based hai to pos == 1 special case.

Pointer ko aage badhana mat bhoolo.

->data compare karo, pointer ko nahi.
